Not much good if you show up at the cliff
and your rope is all bunched in knots. So

00:00:18.439 --> 00:00:22.869
there's the classic mountaineer coil that
you've probably seen, big circular coil over

00:00:22.869 --> 00:00:28.640
somebody's shoulder. I like this coil, it's
a butterfly coil or a butterfly coil. It's

00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:34.410
neat compacted and it doesn't twist the rope.
Let me show you how to do it, surprisingly

00:00:34.410 --> 00:00:40.820
if you just take your rope and pile it on
the ground, it's quite manageable. So I'm

00:00:40.820 --> 00:00:49.019
going to start with the two ends right here
over my shoulders and coil from here without

00:00:49.019 --> 00:00:58.579
ever making a circle by just up and back and
making loops and this won't twist the rope.

00:00:58.579 --> 00:01:05.430
It's doubled because in tight rope climbing
you're mostly going to keep the rope middle

00:01:05.430 --> 00:01:16.210
